	"description": "When you&#x27;re building a webpage, sometimes you might want images or other\nelements to go beyond the boundaries of a container. So in this tutorial, I&#x27;ll\nshow you a couple ways you can accomplish this.\n\nTo illustrate a situation when you might find this useful, let&#x27;s say we are\ngiven a webpage that looks like this:\n\nA webpage whose contents span 100% of the window&#x27;s widthAs you will probably\nagree, that&#x27;s not very pleasant to read. One of the things you can do is set a \nmax-width on the container ",
